						<summary>

						<p>Some stones are lost in the middle. This seems to consist of two records one in continuation of the other, the second one being dated in the 20th year of the king. They both register gifts of 90 sheep for burning 2 perpetual lamps in the temple, each with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee supplied daily.</p>						

